<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/085'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=473 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/085.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/085'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/086'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=470 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/086.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/086'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
The plain white boxes in the scroll bars are called ELEVATORS. Elevators show where you
are in document. For example, an elevator at the top of the vertical scroll bar shows
you&rsquo;re at the document&rsquo;s beginning.
</p><p>
Now scroll using an elevator in the Example window:
<ol>
<li>Click to activate the Example window.
<li>In the right scroll bar, press and hold on the elevator (the white box). Move it down
the scroll bar a bit, then release. Keep doing this until you see &ldquo;THE END.&rdquo;
<li>Move the elevator back to the top of its scroll bar, then release. (Anytime you
release, scrolling stops.) See &ldquo;THE BEGINNING?&rdquo;
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/087'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=475 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/087.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/087'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
In the scroll bars next to the view arrows are the last four scroll symbols. They 
look like tiny pages with a folded corner, and are called VIEW BUTTONS. When you click
or press in a view button, new text appears a &ldquo;windowful&rdquo; at a time, like flipping
pages in a book.
</p><p>
Do this to use view buttons to scroll by windowfuls:
<ol>
<li>Activate the Example window.
<li>In the Example window&rsquo;s right scroll bar, click on the lower view button and
then on the upper view button until you see how they work.
</ol>
</p><p>
You won&rsquo;t need the Example document any more:
<ol start="3">
<li>Put the Example document away. (Activate, choose Save & Put Away from the File/Print menu.)
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/088'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=468 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/088.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/088'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/089'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=466 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/089.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/089'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/090'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=472 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/090.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/090'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/091'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=466 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/091.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/091'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
You&rsquo;ve seen how to move an icon: You can also move a window to any spot on the desktop.
</p><p>
Do this to move the Samples window:
<ol>
<li>Place the pointer&rsquo;s tip in the title bar at the top of the Samples window.
<li>Press and hold as you move the pointer left, straight across the desktop.
<li>When the flickering outline is at the desktop&rsquo;s lower left corner, release the mouse
button. (Stuck? Press Continue, then press Practice when it appears.)
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/092'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=471 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/092.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/092'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/093'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=470 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/093.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/093'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/094'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=473 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/094.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/094'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
You can change the size and shape of a window using the SIZE CONTROL BOX at its lower right
corner.
</p><p>
Make the Samples window as wide as the desktop:
<ol>
<li>Now the Samples window is partly under the LisaGuide window: Click in it to make it active.
<li>Press and hold on Samples&rsquo;s size control box, where the scroll bars intersect.
<li>Move the pointer right: Release when the flickering outline&rsquo;s right edge is at the
desktop&rsquo;s right edge.
</ol>
</p><p>
(To press Continue, activate the LisaGuide window so it will come to the top and you can
see the Continue button.)
</p></td></tr>
