</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/098'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=477 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/098.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/098'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
When working with multiple windows, you can resize and move them to overlap as much or
as little as you please. Note: If you move a window so its scroll bars push against
the desktop&rsquo;s edge, the window will &ldquo;shrink&rdquo; and you may need to resize it.
</p><p>
Resize and move the Samples window:
<ol>
<li>Resize the Samples window so it&rsquo;s just wide enough for its icons to be visible. You&rsquo;ll
first need to activate the window to make its size control box appear. (Stuck? Press
Continue, then press the Practice button when it appears.)
<li>After resizing, move the Samples window to the desktop&rsquo;s lower right corner: It should
just fit.
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
